The local variable 'os_flags' is assigned a value and its address (&os_flags) is passed to setsockopt, but 'os_flags' is not const-qualified even though it is not modified after initialization. According to MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13 it should be declared const (e.g. 'const int os_flags = 1;') so that the pointer effectively points to a const-qualified type.
